notes.note:
This  class meets weekly in person for 2 hours, and the remaining 40 minutes online/asynchronously.

The course is tailored for graduate students in health-related professional schools with basic-to-intermediate proficiency in the Spanish language (102 or equivalent).  It provides intensive communicative proficiency (speaking, listening, reading, writing, and cultural competency) sufficient to provide vital care of patients/clients, in order to best provide them both routine and emergency health services.

SPA522.title: Intro SPA for Health Care Prof

notes.note:
This class meets weekly in person for 2 hours, and the remaining 40 minutes online/asynchronously.
It is tailored for graduate students in health-related professional schools with little or no background in the Spanish language.  It provides beginning communicative proficiency (speaking, listening, reading, writing, and cultural competency) sufficient to provide basic care of patients/clients, in order to provide both routine and emergency health services.

notes.note:
Spring 2022:  Documentary and Literature

Concentrates on the elusive border between documentary (based on fact) and fiction (based on affect and imagination) in modern Spanish literary and filmic texts. Many concern the Spanish Civil War, Franco dictatorship, historical memory, and/or the ¿auto-ficción¿ turn. Taught in Spanish with mainly Spanish texts, including Galdós, Ayala, Cela, Martín Gaite, and Muñoz Molina.
